  <heading>UMULLB (indexed)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Unsigned multiply long by indexed element (bottom)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction multiplies the even-numbered unsigned elements within each 128-bit segment
of the first source vector by the specified unsigned element in the corresponding
second source vector segment, and places the results in the overlapping
double-width elements of the destination vector register.</para>
      <para>The elements within the second source vector are specified using
an immediate index that selects the same element position within
each 128-bit vector segment. The index range is from 0 to
one less than the number of elements per 128-bit segment.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
